race.comment: MAALIS SONG (1) showed good ability in his debut campaign, jumping favourite in his run prior to the break. He looks right up to the mark fresh following a good trial recently and Ramoly knows him well. Has options from the draw and can land the knockout blow. ZALI'S GIFT (8) stuck on well first-up in a 3YO race here a fortnight ago, beaten 0.9L behind what looks a smart one. Fitter for that effort and she drops in weight today. Can make her presence felt. GUARANTOR (3) resumes without a trial but showed enough in his debut campaign. Not out of this as he returns a gelding. ROCKING IN VEGAS (2) has claims third-up into the campaign.
